modules.description: This module displays memory representations of heterogeneous OCaml values using the Kitty terminal graphics protocol. It works with a custom `elist` type that pairs labels and values of arbitrary types, enabling visualization of mixed-type data in a single display call. Concrete use cases include inspecting complex, multi-typed data structures directly in the terminal during debugging or interactive exploration.

This module displays memory representations of OCaml values directly in the Kitty terminal emulator. It supports both homogeneous and heterogeneous data structures through the `show` and `Poly.show` functions, which take labeled value lists and render their layout visually. The module also allows customization of visual properties like colors and layout direction for precise control over the graphical output.
